snippet.textDisplay: One of the best albums made in the last decade. Every song bangs besides Urgency and Pop. Uzi’s music isn’t meant to have deep meanings or life lessons in it its meant to be listened for the sound and the vibe produced which is unbelievable on this album. Baby Pluto, Lo Mein, I’m sorry, celebration station, bigger than life, bust me, prices Venetia all carry this incredible pure energy and melodies to them that just from one listen make you feel in a good mood. Not only this but songs like Pop, Silly Watch, Homecoming, Secure the Bag, You better move all go hard as well and P2 was a deeper and more personal version to XO Tour Llif3 which left an extremely satisfying feeling to an extremely differentiating and vibrant hour of music. Amazing album in my opinion 10/10.

snippet.textDisplay: I reluctantly have to agree with melon on this one, this guy put out songs like xo tour life, the way life goes, even dark queen that had a kind of rhythmic flow but deep sense of melancholy, sadness and disassociation felt in his voice and the lyrics, and this album doesn't evoke many emotions to this level besides disillusionment and hints of sadness that are mostly masked by rapidfire lyrics and spacey beats. I feel like there are hints of Uzi's potential on I'm Sorry, Venetia and P2 but these songs are hidden in the background within the wider concept of the album

snippet.textDisplay: I think that you’re wrong and that Uzi will only grow because of this project. He definitely has paved his own path in the game and there are definitely a few things he does to set himself apart from other artists. Besides, this is only half the FULL album. At least that’s what he told everyone with the deluxe releasing in just 2 days. On top of that he is outselling every other artist by a long shot and competing with the likes of Justin Bieber and Eminem for most first week sales. Uzi is just this kind of artist, it’s a sort of project where if you are an Uzi fan then you should enjoy it. and if not then you probably weren’t that big of a fan in the first place. At first I didn’t think it lived up to the hype but now most of the album has really grown on me and it’s great. The theme is also amazing, after each song there is a tiny skit relating to the theme. And he even stated that he took on 3 different personalities in this project. Baby Pluto (songs 1-6) Renji (songs 7-11) and Uzi (songs 12-18). Finally, it’s only half the album so basically if the deluxe is fire too (which it probably will be) he will solidify himself as one of the best in today’s modern hip-hop culture. And he’ll likely put himself in a position to win some type of award this year. But we’ll have to wait and see because this year is going to be a crazy one for music.
